com.camerontec.catalys.util.notification

Class CatalysEventObject

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.util.EventObject
      • com.camerontec.catalys.util.notification.CatalysEventObject
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, Cloneable
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    ActiveStatusEvent, AttributeChangeEvent, BlockedStatusEvent, ClusterPrimaryStatusEvent, ConfigurationChangeEvent, ConnectionPointEvent, DisconnectRequestedEvent, ExceptionThrownEvent, FixMessageEvent, InMessageReceivedEvent, MessageEvent, NewSessionManagerEvent, ResendStatusEvent, ResetEvent, SessionLifeCycleEvent, UpdatedMessageSeqNumEvent

    public class CatalysEventObject
extends EventObject
implements Cloneable
    Base class for all Catalys events representing a EventObject that supports a writable source, time stamping and an integer type.

      • CatalysEventObject

        public CatalysEventObject(Object source,
                          int type)
        Constructs a Catalys Event.
        Parameters:
        source - The object on which the Event initially occurred. Note that if even if source is serializable it will not be serialized when this event is serialized. If you need to serialize information about the event source consider adding it to the event itself in your concrete subclass.
        type - An int event type or code
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if source is null.

      • equals

        public final boolean equals(Object obj)
        Each is different to another event unless they are the same object or if one of the objects is a clone or deserialized version of the other. This is enforced by comparing the creation timestamp and a unique key given to each new event. This method is final because this algorithm is sufficient to compare any two instances of this base class, regardless of concrete type.
        Overrides:
        equals in class Object

      • clone

        public Object clone()
        This is just a standard shallow copy - achieved by calling Object.clone().

        No assumption is made that attributes of this event are themselves cloneable. We just copy references to any attribute objects.
